trend_summary: Images show a suburban area that steadily urbanised: northern industrial/commercial roofs multiply, residential infill fills central lots, tree cover shrinks, and roads widen. Growth is moderate but continuous, keeping overall fabric medium-density and still green-speckled.
notable_changes: Northern edge transforms from scattered sheds to a large, contiguous warehouse/office park.
Central residential grid tightens as wooded plots become single-family housing and small apartment clusters.
Marked reduction of tree canopy, especially around new rooftops and along widened arterials.
